                        <interp inst="t18791124-name-253" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>HENRY RANDALL</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">Policeman</hi>). I took the defendant on the 6th Dec., at the meeting of creditors, and found this letter in two pieces on him, which was impounded. (<hi rend="italic">This had been torn out of the letter book, and was from the defendant to Mr. Phillips, dated July 30th, stating that he had closed with the offer of</hi> 5,000<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. <hi rend="italic">for the Manchester business</hi>). I found on I him between 2<hi rend="italic">l</hi>. and 3<hi rend="italic">l</hi>., which was given up to him.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18791124-name-254" type="witnessName">
